After his incredible run of women-centric       
films from Chandni Bar, Page 3, Satta and       
Corporate to the blockbuster Fashion, Madhur    
Bhandarkar now turns his lens inwards and       
presents his most ambitious work yet - Heroine. 
The film is based on the life and times of a    
superstar heroine from the dream factory we     
call 'Bollywood'. The film is a daring,         
shocking, glamorous, scandalous behind the      
scenes account of the reality behind the world  
of glitz and glamour that our film stars inhabit
For a country obsessed with films and film stars
Heroine will take audiences on a voyeuristic    
journey to see what really goes on behind the   
closed doors of make up rooms and vanity vans.  


